<simulation>
    <width>8</width>
    <height>8</height>
    <gameType>Spreading of Fire</gameType>
    <title>Spreading of Fire Simulation</title>
    <author>B Drossel, F Schwabl </author>
    <probFillTree>0.4</probFillTree>
    <probCatch>0.2</probCatch>
    <language>French</language>
    <description>
        The Spreading of Fire simulation models the dynamic propagation of fire in a forest, with cells representing empty spaces, living trees, or burning trees. Trees can catch fire from neighboring burning cells or spontaneously ignite, while empty spaces may be filled with new trees.

        White = Empty
        Green = Tree
        Red = Fire
        Chance of empty land growing a tree = 40%
        Chance of tree catching fire = 20%
    </description>
